 a \cos x + b \sin x = \sqrt{a^2 + b^2} \left ( \frac a{\sqrt{a^2 + b^2}} \cos x + \frac b{\sqrt{a^2 + b^2}} \sin x\right ) = \\ = \sqrt{a^2 + b^2} \left ( \cos t \cos x + \sin t \sin x \right ) = \sqrt{a^2 + b^2} \cos (x - t) 
